  displayName: Berberoka
  description: Found in water-centered folklore, berberoka is often portrayed as
    an ambush predator that uses marshes, rivers, and sudden floods to entrap victims.
    Narrative emphasis is placed on cunning behavior rather than open confrontation.
    Culturally, the legend serves as a warning about deceptive calm in wetland environments
    and the hidden danger beneath still water.
